SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 369
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to recognize Mattie Cook on the occasion of her
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should honor those citizens who have performed
with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their years of industry; and
WHEREAS, Mattie Cook is one such estimable person who served with distinction for
fifty years as a custodian with the Sevier County School System and took her much-deserved
retirement on February 28, 2025; and
WHEREAS, during her tenure as custodian at Parkway Academy and the adult
education building on Cedar Street in Sevierville, Mattie Cook truly served as an inspiration to
her colleagues, and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to
know her; and
WHEREAS, a beloved family matriarch, Ms. Cook plans to spend her retirement keeping
busy, doing more community service work alongside her daughter, visiting rest homes, and
taking care of her church; and
WHEREAS, Mattie Cook exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community
that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, Mattie Cook epitomizes the dedicated professional who is wholly committed
to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we extend to Mattie Cook our heartfelt wishes for a
happy and fulfilling retirement and every continued success in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
